snippet: The Czech Supreme Court ruled that Petr Necas was not entitled to immunity from prosecution on possible corruption charges.
abstract: Czech Supreme Court rules that former Prime Min Petr Necas is not entitled to immunity from prosecution for the period when he was head of government, clearing way for him to be charged with corruption.
lead_paragraph: The Czech Supreme Court ruled that Petr Necas was not entitled to immunity from prosecution on possible corruption charges.

headline.main: Former Premier Can Be Charged, Czech Court Rules
headline.print_headline:
Czech Republic: Supreme Court
Says Ex-Leader Can Be Prosecuted
